Carmean has registered one career goal, coming in her sophomore season. Zakiya Chambers-Hunter – Solomons, Md. A three-time member of the Atlantic Sun Honor Roll, Chambers-Hunter has been a reserve goalkeeper for the past three seasons, for three of those seasons; Chambers-Hunter also was a member of the North Florida Women's Basketball team. Amanda Fischler – Tallahassee, Fla. A three-time member of the Atlantic Sun Honor Roll and a four-year letterwinner for the Ospreys, Fischler has shown to be a midfielder who can occasionally find the back of the net. Fischler has registered two goals and three assists in her career. She registered her first career goal last season in a win over USC Upstate. Lanie Keating – Longwood, Fla. A three-time member of the Atlantic Sun Honor Roll and a four-year letterwinner for the Ospreys, Keating has been an emerging presence on the defense and as a specialist. Keating has made 42 starts over the course of her career out of 54 appearances. Last season, Keating earned A-Sun Defensive Player of the Week. This year she has registered one goal while leading the team in shots and shots-on-goal. For her performance on the field, in the classroom, and in the community, was recognized by the Atlantic Sun on their 2014-2015 Winners for Life team.
